# NightmareSceneSetup Design

## Purpose
One-click editor tool (`TraeTools > Setup Nightmare Scene`) that configures the full game scene from scratch on top of the SimpleNaturePack demo scene.

## Execution Order
1. Open `SimpleNaturePack_Demo.unity`
2. Fix all materials → URP/Lit
3. Clean up old objects (cameras, controllers, event systems)
4. Darken ambient lighting
5. Scale world (WorldRoot × 20)
6. Instantiate player (Casual1.prefab) at safe spawn point
7. Set up animator controller with all animation states
8. Create main camera + ThirdPersonCamera
9. Spawn weapon pickup (Rusty Knife)
10. Spawn enemy (Pumpkin King + EnemyAI)
11. Set up KCP network layer (NanoKcpClient + NetworkPlayerManager)
12. Create mobile controls canvas
13. Save scene + add to build settings

## Constraints
- Scene target is always `SimpleNaturePack_Demo.unity` — do not change without updating all spawn coordinates
- Safe spawn position `(82, 15, -50)` is tuned for the scaled ×20 world — update `GameConstants.SafeSpawnPos` if scene changes
- No Netcode/NetworkManager — KCP is the only network system
- `CreateNanoKcpClientScript()` will NOT overwrite existing `NanoKcpClient.cs` to preserve manual edits
- Materials are force-upgraded to URP/Lit; nature assets use alpha-clip for leaves/grass
- Animation FBX files are imported from Mixamo — loop settings are controlled via `SetFBXLoopTime()`

## When Modifying
- If adding a new setup step, make it a separate static method and call it from `SetupScene()`
- Keep the method idempotent — running setup twice should produce the same result
- Always check for existing objects before creating (find + destroy pattern)
